{"questionId":"22437061","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>At another building site, the time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> hours, it takes to lay bricks varies inversely with the number of bricklayers, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Five bricklayers take <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn></math> hours to lay an area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate how long it takes <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>12</mn></math> bricklayers to lay an area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>expressing <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> terms of reciprocal of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>B</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;</em>OR<em>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>∝</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>B</mi></mfrac></math></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mn>5</mn></mfrac></math></em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>40</mn></math><br></em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mn>40</mn><mn>12</mn></mfrac><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>33333</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math> (hours)&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> hours <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>20</mn></math> minutes&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award at most <strong><em>M1A1A0</em></strong> for the use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>B</mi></math> in part (b) if <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi>k</mi><mi>B</mi></mfrac></math> was seen and penalized in part (a).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22437061","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.4b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate how long it takes 12 bricklayers to lay an area of 60 m2.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}